I spoke w/a few founders recently who got screwed by investors. A few rules of thumb for pre-seed/seed:
- ~20% dilution is normal. 30% is ok. 50+% is crazy.
- $ only counts when it's in the bank. Deals do fall through last minute.
- If a VC can't wire for 30+ days, keep looking.

text:
Once the vaccine becomes available, one of the biggest ethical dilemmas for Govts will be how to deal with those who deny vaccination.

Assuming the vaccine is effective, how would Govts deal with the burden on the healthcare system by those who don't want to get vaccinated.

text: (3) Given the accurate trackability of each delivery hero (present location, residence, delivery path, etc), even in today's unfortunate incident, all potentially affected individuals were identified promptly and quarantined. Can't do that with anonymous spreaders in the markets.

text: 3/4. Interestingly only 2 months after the website went live, my father got a lead for an export order from Europe which thereafter changed the fate of his business. That company which helped him take his modest manufacturing business international was @IndiaMART.

name: Kunal Bahl
text: 2/4. I recall the beeming sales person being very patient w/me, never annoyed by a nitpicking 15 year old. I thought that this is an incredible company. They not only come to your office/home, work on multiple versions of your website and then also bring more customers to you.

name: Kunal Bahl
text: 1/4. In 1998, I was in 10th and my father asked me to get a website made for him, as a small "web design" company from Noida had contacted him and told him that it will help him get more business. I spent a lot of time going through various versions of the website, colour schemes
